  "prompt": "Should one say \"runners-up\" or \"runner-ups\"?",
  "response": "The correct plural form is \"runners-up.\" \n\nIn this compound noun, \"runner\" is the main noun, and \"up\" is a prepositional element. When forming the plural, the primary noun \"runner\" takes the plural form, while \"up\" remains unchanged. Therefore, you should say \"runners-up\" when referring to multiple individuals or teams who finished in second place or as finalists. \n\nFor example: \n- \"The runners-up in the competition received silver medals.\" \n- \"Both teams were declared runners-up after the final match.\" \n\nUsing \"runner-ups\" is considered incorrect in standard English usage.",
